                <h2>What is Early Bird Check-In on Southwest Airlines?</h2>
                <p>Well, this airline does not assign seats in advance. Instead, passengers are assigned a boarding group (A, B, or C) and a position (1–60) based on when they check-in. While selecting the early bird check-in, the airline automatically checks you in 36 hours before departure, which is 12 hours earlier than standard check-in. This helps you to get a better boarding position and more seating choices.</p>
